President Obama held a video teleconference with the leaders of the United Kingdom, France, Germany, and Italy to discuss various global issues. They discussed the crisis in Ukraine and stressed the need for unrestricted access to the site of the Malaysia Airlines Flight 17 crash. They also agreed on the importance of coordinated sanctions on Russia for its involvement in Ukraine. The leaders also discussed the situation in Gaza and called for an immediate, unconditional humanitarian ceasefire. They discussed the security challenges in Iraq and urged the formation of an inclusive government. Lastly, they talked about the need for a ceasefire among militias in Libya and expressed support for the UN's efforts to resolve the conflict.